messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
There's a fire right here off of Broadway.
Broadway and 4th Street. There's a girl that's unconscious.
Okay, Broadway and 4th. Are you guys in a building, somewhere on the sidewalk, where?
Everybody is outside.
Did anybody have any weapons? Do we know how she went unconscious?
No, there were guys and girls hitting her.
Okay, let me start the paramedics. Hang on. Don't hang up, okay?
Stay on the line. I'm going to get paramedics, and then I have more questions for you, okay?
She's breathing. She just took a deep breath in.
Ma'am, is she on the sidewalk or in the street?
She's on the sidewalk. She's taking deep breaths in.
There's a lot of people here.
Do you know which people were hitting her so we can try to get them?
Everybody just ran off. Security is trying to get people that ran off.
Do you have a description of those people, males, females?
They were Asians, Asian men and women.
Roughly how old were they?
They're probably either 23, 24.
And security is trying to get those people?
Yes.
Which way did they go?
They ran down 4th Street towards Main.
Do you know if any of those people used any weapons?
I don't know any of these people. I just took the phone from one of her friends. She didn't know what to do. I told her to call 911, and I called for her.
Can you give me a description of the injured lady?
She seems about 23 or 24 years old. She's wearing black pants, a black shirt, a jean jacket. She's Asian, Vietnamese.
Is she at the corner of Broadway and 4th, in front of which business?
Right in front of the Crosby.
And her friends are with her?
Yes, her friends are with her.
And what is your name?
I just saw guys and girls hitting her. We just walked out of the club, and I don't know what happened. I just saw that they were hitting somebody.
And the phone number you're calling me from is just one that you borrowed, right?
Yeah, I don't know whose phone it is. I know that it was one of her friends because they were crying that they don't know what to do.
She's still there, right at Broadway and 4th?
She's here on the sidewalk, still unconscious, but she's breathing.
The officers are already on the line with her, just to make sure that she's okay. And security is with her, correct?
No, there's one standing around, but they're not with her.
Okay, we'll get police officers there.
They didn't even know what to do.
I've got an officer there now. He should be pulling up right now. Do you see him at all?
I see him, yeah.
Can you flag him down?
Okay, he's here.
Okay, does he see you guys?
Yes, he's just getting out of the car.
Okay, I'm going to go ahead and disconnect now. Thank you.
Okay, thank you.
